course_title: Theoretical Perspectives in Nursing: Childbearing Individuals and their Families

002.building: P. A. Woodward Instructional Resources Centre

description: Analysis and application of theories, concepts, evidence and competencies guiding professional nursing practice with childbearing individuals and families during the transition to parenthood in a variety of practice settings and contexts. Students who take NURS 345 cannot earn credit for NURS 333 or NURS 422. This course is eligible for Cr/F for 19W2 only.
